<p><b>Textpattern</b> is an <a href="/wiki/Open_source" title="Open source">open source</a> <a href="/wiki/Content_management_system" title="Content management system">content management system</a> originally developed by Dean Allen. While it is often listed among <a href="/wiki/Weblogging" title="Weblogging" class="mw-redirect">weblogging</a> tools, its aim is to be a high-quality general-purpose <a href="/wiki/Content_management_system" title="Content management system">content management system</a> suitable for deployment in many contexts. Textpattern is written in <a href="/wiki/PHP" title="PHP">PHP</a> using a <a href="/wiki/MySQL" title="MySQL">MySQL</a> database backend, and versions from "gamma" 1.19 through 4.0.<i>x</i> are distributed under the <a href="/wiki/GNU_General_Public_License" title="GNU General Public License">GNU General Public License</a>; however, future versions beginning with 4.1 will be distributed under the <a href="/wiki/BSD_license" title="BSD license" class="mw-redirect">BSD license</a><sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>. The current stable version is Textpattern 4.0.8</p>
